## Task: Set up npm/tsc/vitest/happy-dom toolchain and CSS copy script
## Step: review

### package.json
```json
{
  "name": "filebrowser-ui",
  "private": true,
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "type": "module",
  "scripts": {
    "build": "tsc && node scripts/copy-assets.mjs",
    "test": "vitest run",
    "watch": "tsc --watch"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "typescript": "^5.6.3",
    "vitest": "^2.1.4",
    "happy-dom": "^15.7.4"
  }
}

```
### tsconfig.json
```json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "target": "ES2022",
    "module": "ESNext",
    "moduleResolution": "Bundler",
    "strict": true,
    "outDir": "wwwroot/dist",
    "rootDir": "src",
    "sourceMap": true,
    "lib": ["ES2022", "DOM", "DOM.Iterable"],
    "esModuleInterop": true,
    "forceConsistentCasingInFileNames": true,
    "skipLibCheck": true,
    "noEmitOnError": true
  },
  "include": ["src/**/*.ts"],
  "exclude": ["src/**/*.test.ts", "node_modules", "wwwroot"]
}

```
### vitest.config.ts
```typescript
import { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config';

export default defineConfig({
  test: {
    environment: 'happy-dom',
    include: ['src/**/*.test.ts']
  }
});

```
### scripts/copy-assets.mjs
```mjs
import { mkdir, copyFile } from 'node:fs/promises';
import { resolve, dirname } from 'node:path';
import { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';

const __filename = fileURLToPath(import.meta.url);
const __dirname = dirname(__filename);

const rootDir = resolve(__dirname, '..');
const srcDir = resolve(rootDir, 'src');
const outDir = resolve(rootDir, 'wwwroot', 'dist');

async function main() {
  // Ensure output directory exists
  await mkdir(outDir, { recursive: true });

  const srcPath = resolve(srcDir, 'app.css');
  const destPath = resolve(outDir, 'app.css');

  try {
    await copyFile(srcPath, destPath);
  } catch {
    // If src/app.css doesn't exist, exit 0 silently
    process.exit(0);
  }
}

main();

```
Create four files at the repo root (NOT under artifacts). (1) package.json: `{ "name": "filebrowser-ui", "private": true, "version": "1.0.0", "type": "module", "scripts": { "build": "tsc && node scripts/copy-assets.mjs", "test": "vitest run", "watch": "tsc --watch" }, "devDependencies": { "typescript": "^5.6.3", "vitest": "^2.1.4", "happy-dom": "^15.7.4" } }`. (2) tsconfig.json with compilerOptions: target "ES2022", module "ESNext", moduleResolution "Bundler", strict true, outDir "wwwroot/dist", rootDir "src", sourceMap true, lib ["ES2022","DOM","DOM.Iterable"], esModuleInterop true, forceConsistentCasingInFileNames true, skipLibCheck true, noEmitOnError true; include ["src/**/*.ts"]; exclude ["src/**/*.test.ts", "node_modules", "wwwroot"]. (3) vitest.config.ts: `import { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config'; export default defineConfig({ test: { environment: 'happy-dom', include: ['src/**/*.test.ts'] } });`. (4) scripts/copy-assets.mjs: an ESM script using node:fs/promises and node:path that ensures wwwroot/dist exists (mkdir recursive) and copies src/app.css to wwwroot/dist/app.css IF src/app.css exists, otherwise exits 0 silently (so builds before the CSS task don't fail). After creating the files run `npm install` to install devDependencies. NOTE for downstream tasks: because the build emits native browser ESM with no bundler, all relative TypeScript imports MUST use a `.js` extension (e.g. `import { ApiClient } from './api.js'`). Verify: `npm install` exits 0 and `node scripts/copy-assets.mjs` exits 0 (no-op since no css yet).

## Response Format (required)
Respond with ONLY a single valid JSON object matching the schema below.
- No prose, explanations, or commentary before or after the JSON.
- No markdown code fences (```), no headings — output the raw JSON object.
- Do NOT call any tools and do NOT end your turn on a thinking block. Emit the JSON object directly as text.

JSON schema:
{ approved: Whether the implementation is accepted, feedback: Detailed review feedback, issues: Array<{ file: File with the issue, description: What needs to be fixed, severity: "critical" | "minor" /* How important the fix is */ }> }

import { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config';

export default defineConfig({
  test: {
    environment: 'happy-dom',
    include: ['src/**/*.test.ts']
  }
});

import { mkdir, copyFile } from 'node:fs/promises';
import { resolve, dirname } from 'node:path';
import { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';

const __filename = fileURLToPath(import.meta.url);
const __dirname = dirname(__filename);

const rootDir = resolve(__dirname, '..');
const srcDir = resolve(rootDir, 'src');
const outDir = resolve(rootDir, 'wwwroot', 'dist');

async function main() {
  // Ensure output directory exists
  await mkdir(outDir, { recursive: true });

  const srcPath = resolve(srcDir, 'app.css');
  const destPath = resolve(outDir, 'app.css');

  try {
    await copyFile(srcPath, destPath);
  } catch {
    // If src/app.css doesn't exist, exit 0 silently
    process.exit(0);
  }
}

main();

All four files exist at the repo root with content matching the specification exactly, `npm install` succeeded (happy-dom, typescript, vitest all present), and `node scripts/copy-assets.mjs` exits 0 (and correctly copies `src/app.css` to `wwwroot/dist/app.css` when present). I have one minor robustness note.

```json
{
  "approved": true,
  "feedback": "Implementation is complete and matches the task specification. All four artifacts are present at the repo root (not under artifacts/): (1) package.json with the required name, scripts (build/test/watch), and devDependencies pinned to the specified ranges; (2) tsconfig.json with all required compilerOptions (target ES2022, module ESNext, moduleResolution Bundler, strict, outDir wwwroot/dist, rootDir src, sourceMap, lib ES2022/DOM/DOM.Iterable, esModuleInterop, forceConsistentCasingInFileNames, skipLibCheck, noEmitOnError), include and exclude globs; (3) vitest.config.ts using defineConfig with happy-dom environment and the correct test include pattern; (4) scripts/copy-assets.mjs as an ESM script using node:fs/promises and node:path that mkdir -p's wwwroot/dist and copies src/app.css -> wwwroot/dist/app.css, swallowing ENOENT-style errors with process.exit(0). Verification passed: `npm ls` shows happy-dom@15.11.7, typescript@5.9.3, vitest@2.1.9 installed, and `node scripts/copy-assets.mjs` exits 0. Conventions are followed (ESM, node: protocol imports, no leftover debug statements, no dead code). One minor note below regarding unhandled-rejection surface on the top-level `main()` call; this is not a blocker and matches the spec verbatim, so do not expand scope to address it if it deviates from the prescribed snippet.",
  "issues": [
    {
      "file": "scripts/copy-assets.mjs",
      "description": "The top-level `main()` call is fire-and-forget: its returned Promise is neither awaited nor given a `.catch()` handler. The try/catch only guards `copyFile`, so if `mkdir(outDir, { recursive: true })` rejects (e.g., permission denied, invalid path), the rejection becomes unhandled and Node may exit with a non-zero code and a confusing stderr message rather than the intended silent exit-0 behavior. Consider `main().catch(() => process.exit(0));` or awaiting main inside an entrypoint guard. Minor since it matches the spec snippet exactly and only matters under unusual filesystem errors.",
      "severity": "minor"
    }
  ]
}
```
